main event: On January 8, 1958, a UFO was sighted in Deland, Florida, described as a round, fuzzy object with an orange, rose tint, observed for approximately 2 to 5 minutes.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be the size of Mars,The sighting lasted for about 2-5 minutes and occurred around 12:30 EST,The object flew at a very high rate of speed before disappearing,There were several witnesses in Deland, Florida,The case was ultimately marked as insufficient evidence with the possibility of the object being Venus.
sighted object: round fuzzy object with an orange, rosy tint
witness description: Numerous people observed the event in the area.
